3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper may involve concepts from information theory, such as entropy, as regular languages can be viewed as a type of code. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper involves analyzing the complexities of operations on regular languages, which can be viewed as a type of computational problem.
